     1→====================================================
     2→pluggy - A minimalist production ready plugin system
     3→====================================================
     4→
     5→|pypi| |conda-forge| |versions| |github-actions| |gitter| |black| |codecov|
     6→
     7→This is the core framework used by the `pytest`_, `tox`_, and `devpi`_ projects.
     8→
     9→Please `read the docs`_ to learn more!
    10→
    11→A definitive example
    12→====================
    13→.. code-block:: python
    14→
    15→    import pluggy
    16→
    17→    hookspec = pluggy.HookspecMarker("myproject")
    18→    hookimpl = pluggy.HookimplMarker("myproject")
    19→
    20→
    21→    class MySpec:
    22→        """A hook specification namespace."""
    23→
    24→        @hookspec
    25→        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    26→            """My special little hook that you can customize."""
    27→
    28→
    29→    class Plugin_1:
    30→        """A hook implementation namespace."""
    31→
    32→        @hookimpl
    33→        def myhook(self, arg1, arg2):
    34→            print("inside Plugin_1.myhook()")
    35→            return arg1 + arg2
    36→
